<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 04 at 1:42AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Moderate to heavy snow will impact northern Gallatin County
through 245 AM MST...
At 139 AM MST, Doppler radar was tracking snow bands over the
Bozeman area.
HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph. Snow, with visibility below one half
mile at times.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Visibility below one half mile and slippery roads.
Locations impacted
include... Bozeman, Belgrade, Three Forks, Manhattan,
Bozeman Hot Springs, Gallatin Gateway.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 90 between mile markers 277 and 321.
Highway 191 between mile markers 65 and 87.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>Use caution if traveling.</instruction>
